They dress in white. They wear floppy hats. And they also don fake fist-long beards. With a beer in hand, they scream “Hashim! Hashim! Hashim! Hashim! Hashim”. They call themselves the #AmlaArmy. And they are South Africa’s answer to the much vaunted #BarmyArmy  In this remarkable video from day 2 at Newlands,  the #AmlaArmy face off with the #BarmyArmy. If you listen carefully, every chant of Hashim is met with a equally shrilling “Moeen”, in reference to that other bearded bloke, Moeen Ali. Only in South Africa